\pard\plain\ltrpar\ql\sl240\slmult1\itap0{\f0\fs24\b\lang2057{\*\listtag0}\abinodiroverride\ltrch An audio event space, signal preparation, alerting & more}{\f0\fs24\b\lang2057{\*\listtag0}\par}
\pard\plain\ltrpar\ql\sl240\slmult1\itap0{\f0\fs24\b\lang2057{\*\listtag0}\par}
\pard\plain\ltrpar\ql\sl240\slmult1\itap0{\f0\fs24\lang2057{\*\listtag0}\abinodiroverride\ltrch The primary function of the sequencer is to provide a location for which audio events can be loaded, positioned and adjusted in comparison to other relatively loaded events. These events are then used in the replay of a production to ensure that events are triggered as they are scheduled to occur.}{\f0\fs24\lang2057{\*\listtag0}\par}
\pard\plain\ltrpar\ql\sl240\slmult1\itap0{\f0\fs24\lang2057{\*\listtag0}\par}
\pard\plain\ltrpar\ql\sl240\slmult1\itap0{\f0\fs24\lang2057{\*\listtag0}\abinodiroverride\ltrch As the sequencer is designed to be used in a variety of situations, preparing of upcoming events is a key element which allows for situations where the audio needs to be }{\f0\fs24\lang3081{\*\listtag0}synthesised}{\f0\fs24\lang2057{\*\listtag0} in anticipation of the event and or to accommodate changes in the audio output over time.}{\f0\fs24\lang2057{\*\listtag0}\par}
\pard\plain\ltrpar\ql\sl240\slmult1\itap0{\f0\fs24\lang2057{\*\listtag0}\par}
\pard\plain\ltrpar\ql\sl240\slmult1\itap0{\f0\fs24\b\lang2057{\*\listtag0}\abinodiroverride\ltrch Setup}{\f0\fs24\b\lang2057{\*\listtag0}\par}
\pard\plain\ltrpar\ql\sl240\slmult1\itap0{\f0\fs24\b\lang2057{\*\listtag0}\par}
\pard\plain\ltrpar\ql\sl240\slmult1\itap0{\f0\fs24\lang2057{\*\listtag0}\abinodiroverride\ltrch The sequencer is broken in to a number of elements which combine to provide the base functionality for audio triggering and composition playback.}{\f0\fs24\lang2057{\*\listtag0}\par}
\pard\plain\ltrpar\ql\sl240\slmult1\itap0{\f0\fs24\lang2057{\*\listtag0}\par}
\pard\plain\ltrpar\ql\sl240\slmult1\itap0{\f0\fs24\b\lang2057{\*\listtag0}\abinodiroverride\ltrch Timing (Time Codes)}{\f0\fs24\b\lang2057{\*\listtag0}\par}
\pard\plain\ltrpar\ql\sl240\slmult1\itap0{\f0\fs24\b\lang2057{\*\listtag0}\par}
\pard\plain\ltrpar\ql\sl240\slmult1\itap0{\f0\fs24\lang2057{\*\listtag0}\abinodiroverride\ltrch Timing within a composition is archived by using a base positioning mechanism. The base measurement for the composition is calculated in nanoseconds:}{\f0\fs24\lang2057{\*\listtag0}\par}
\pard\plain\ltrpar\ql\sl240\slmult1\itap0{\f0\fs24\lang2057{\*\listtag0}\par}
\pard\plain\ltrpar\ql\sl240\slmult1\itap0{\f0\fs24\lang2057{\*\listtag0}\abinodiroverride\ltrch 1 second = 1 000 milliseconds}{\f0\fs24\lang2057{\*\listtag0}\par}
\pard\plain\ltrpar\ql\sl240\slmult1\itap0{\f0\fs24\lang2057{\*\listtag0}\abinodiroverride\ltrch 1 millisecond = 1 000 microseconds}{\f0\fs24\lang2057{\*\listtag0}\par}
\pard\plain\ltrpar\ql\sl240\slmult1\itap0{\f0\fs24\lang2057{\*\listtag0}\abinodiroverride\ltrch 1 microsecond = 1 000 nanoseconds}{\f0\fs24\lang2057{\*\listtag0}\par}
\pard\plain\ltrpar\ql\sl240\slmult1\itap0{\f0\fs24\lang2057{\*\listtag0}\par}
\pard\plain\ltrpar\ql\sl240\slmult1\itap0{\f0\fs24\lang2057{\*\listtag0}\abinodiroverride\ltrch As such the base positioning mechanism uses  Int64 variables to calculate the offset of events, from the initial position of 0. }{\f0\fs24\lang2057{\*\listtag0}\par}
\pard\plain\ltrpar\ql\sl240\slmult1\itap0{\f0\fs24\lang2057{\*\listtag0}\par}
\pard\plain\ltrpar\ql\sl240\slmult1\itap0{\f0\fs24\lang3081{\*\listtag0}\abinodiroverride\ltrch In the .Net framework th}{\f0\fs24\lang2057{\*\listtag0}e Int64 }{\f0\fs24\lang3081{\*\listtag0}data }{\f0\fs24\lang2057{\*\listtag0}type allows for a maximum value of 9,223,372,036,854,775,807. Which provides for a composition of over 292 years in duration when calculating from a base of nanoseconds [excessively big \uc1\u8211\'96 yes].}{\f0\fs24\lang3081{\*\listtag0}\par}
\pard\plain\ltrpar\ql\sl240\slmult1\itap0{\f0\fs24\lang2057{\*\listtag0}\par}
\pard\plain\ltrpar\ql\sl240\slmult1\itap0{\f0\fs24\lang2057{\*\listtag0}\abinodiroverride\ltrch 9,223,372,036,854,775,807 nanoseconds / 1000 = 9223372036854775.807 microseconds}{\f0\fs24\lang2057{\*\listtag0}\par}
\pard\plain\ltrpar\ql\sl240\slmult1\itap0{\f0\fs24\lang2057{\*\listtag0}\abinodiroverride\ltrch 9223372036854775.807 microseconds / 1000 = 9223372036854.7758 milliseconds}{\f0\fs24\lang2057{\*\listtag0}\par}
\pard\plain\ltrpar\ql\sl240\slmult1\itap0{\f0\fs24\lang2057{\*\listtag0}\abinodiroverride\ltrch 9223372036854.7758 milliseconds / 1000 = 9223372036.8547 seconds}{\f0\fs24\lang2057{\*\listtag0}\par}
\pard\plain\ltrpar\ql\sl240\slmult1\itap0{\f0\fs24\lang2057{\*\listtag0}\abinodiroverride\ltrch 9223372036.8547 seconds / 60 = 153722867.2809 minutes}{\f0\fs24\lang2057{\*\listtag0}\par}
\pard\plain\ltrpar\ql\sl240\slmult1\itap0{\f0\fs24\lang2057{\*\listtag0}\abinodiroverride\ltrch 153722867.2809 minutes / 60 = 2562047.7880 hours}{\f0\fs24\lang2057{\*\listtag0}\par}
\pard\plain\ltrpar\ql\sl240\slmult1\itap0{\f0\fs24\lang2057{\*\listtag0}\abinodiroverride\ltrch 2562047.7880 hours / 24 = 106751.9911 days}{\f0\fs24\lang2057{\*\listtag0}\par}
\pard\plain\ltrpar\ql\sl240\slmult1\itap0{\f0\fs24\lang2057{\*\listtag0}\abinodiroverride\ltrch 106751.9911 days / 365 = 292.4712 years}{\f0\fs24\lang2057{\*\listtag0}\par}
\pard\plain\ltrpar\ql\sl240\slmult1\itap0{\f0\fs24\lang2057{\*\listtag0}\par}
\pard\plain\ltrpar\ql\sl240\slmult1\itap0{\f0\fs24\lang2057{\*\listtag0}\abinodiroverride\ltrch Each position represents a Time Code, for which events can be aligned to and is calculated as an offset from 0, which is the starting Time Code position.}{\f0\fs24\lang2057{\*\listtag0}\par}
\pard\plain\ltrpar\ql\sl240\slmult1\itap0{\f0\fs24\lang2057{\*\listtag0}\par}
\pard\plain\ltrpar\ql\sl240\slmult1\itap0{\f0\fs24\b\lang2057{\*\listtag0}\abinodiroverride\ltrch Base Beats Per Minute (BPM)}{\f0\fs24\b\lang2057{\*\listtag0}\par}
\pard\plain\ltrpar\ql\sl240\slmult1\itap0{\f0\fs24\b\lang2057{\*\listtag0}\par}
\pard\plain\ltrpar\ql\sl240\slmult1\itap0{\f0\fs24\lang2057{\*\listtag0}\abinodiroverride\ltrch Each composition has a base BPM, it is effectively initialised from position 0. It is initialised to provide a standard reference-able count of beats such that events can be quantised against composition if required.}{\f0\fs24\lang2057{\*\listtag0}\par}
\pard\plain\ltrpar\ql\sl240\slmult1\itap0{\f0\fs24\lang2057{\*\listtag0}\par}
\pard\plain\ltrpar\ql\sl240\slmult1\itap0{\f0\fs24\lang2057{\*\listtag0}\abinodiroverride\ltrch The BPM is not used to control or calculate play back as the events will be }{\f0\fs24\lang3081{\*\listtag0}initialised}{\f0\fs24\lang2057{\*\listtag0} based on their time code offset.}{\f0\fs24\lang2057{\*\listtag0}\par}
\pard\plain\ltrpar\ql\sl240\slmult1\itap0{\f0\fs24\lang2057{\*\listtag0}\par}
\pard\plain\ltrpar\ql\sl240\slmult1\itap0{\f0\fs24\b\lang2057{\*\listtag0}\abinodiroverride\ltrch Variable BPM}{\f0\fs24\b\lang2057{\*\listtag0}\par}
\pard\plain\ltrpar\ql\sl240\slmult1\itap0{\f0\fs24\b\lang2057{\*\listtag0}\par}
\pard\plain\ltrpar\ql\sl240\slmult1\itap0{\f0\fs24\lang2057{\*\listtag0}\abinodiroverride\ltrch Although a Base BPM is initialised for the composition, this value can be overridden at any Time Code through the composition. This allows for melody's which require a true shift in the BPM rating over time rather than defining a constant value for the composition. When }{\f0\fs24\lang3081{\*\listtag0}quantising}{\f0\fs24\lang2057{\*\listtag0} events, the position of each BPM variation is taken in to account and calculated forward from the position change.}{\f0\fs24\lang2057{\*\listtag0}\par}
