\pard\plain\ltrpar\ql\sl240\slmult1\itap0{\f0\fs24\b\lang2057{\*\listtag0}\par}
\pard\plain\ltrpar\ql\sl240\slmult1\itap0{\f0\fs24\lang2057{\*\listtag0}\abinodiroverride\ltrch A track is a collection of Events which is placed in the composition, from the starting Time Code offset. Each Event loaded in to a track is offset from the Time Code for the track; not the starting Time Code for the composition (which is always 0). As such}{\f0\fs24\lang3081{\*\listtag0},}{\f0\fs24\lang2057{\*\listtag0} tracks can be moved independently on the composition, keeping all of the Events encapsulated within the track sequenced correctly regardless of where the track is positioned within the composition itself. }{\f0\fs24\lang2057{\*\listtag0}\par}
\pard\plain\ltrpar\ql\sl240\slmult1\itap0{\f0\fs24\lang2057{\*\listtag0}\par}
\pard\plain\ltrpar\ql\sl240\slmult1\itap0{\f0\fs24\lang2057{\*\listtag0}\abinodiroverride\ltrch Each composition requires at least one track, the default of which is track 0.}{\f0\fs24\lang2057{\*\listtag0}\par}
\pard\plain\ltrpar\ql\sl240\slmult1\itap0{\f0\fs24\lang2057{\*\listtag0}\par}
